base s ggplot2

  • az R alapjraton tartalmaz brzolsra hasznlhat fggvnyeket s emellett van egy nagyon kedvelt package, a ggplot2, ami kifejezetten vizualizcis cl
  • hogy melyik hasznlata a jobb, egyrszt clfgg, msrszt attl is fgg, hogy ki mit szokott meg:
  • http://flowingdata.com/2016/03/22/comparing-ggplot2-and-r-base-graphics/
  • http://varianceexplained.org/r/why-I-use-ggplot2/
  • http://simplystatistics.org/2016/02/11/why-i-dont-use-ggplot2/
  • az adatokkal ismerkeds kzben sokan maradnak a base package fggvnyeinl, mert gyorsan ad valamilyen kpet az adatokrl, s nem fontos, hogy szp legyen a plot
  • ha mr elkezdjk szptgetni a plotokat, a ggplot2 lehetsgeivel knnyebb dolgunk lehet
  • a ggplot2 elnye, hogy az n. grammar of graphics nyelvezett hasznlja, ami egy konzisztens grafikai rendszert pt ki s ms vizualizcis toolok is hasznljk
  • amiket nem lehet velk, ms package-ek szksgesek:
  • 3D plotok (pl. rgl, scatterplot3d)
  • hlzatok (pl. igraph, d3Network, ggnet2)
  • interaktv plotok (pl. ggvis, d3r, plotly)

Adatok elksztse a vizualizcikhoz

  • vizualizlni leginkbb data frame objektumokat szoktunk, de package-tl fggen mtrixokat, vektorokat is
  • a data frame-eknek van egy n. szles s hossz formja (wide and long format), a ggplot2 utbbit preferlja

Data frame talaktsa reshape2-vel

  • tbb lehetsg is van r: http://www.cookbook-r.com/Manipulating_data/Converting_data_between_wide_and_long_format/
  • reshape2 package melt fggvnyvel nznk pldt
#---Adatok elksztse a vizualizcikhoz--------------------------------------
# reshape2 installlsa s behvsa
# install.packages("reshape2", dependencies = TRUE)
library(reshape2)

# data frame ltrehozsa - wide format
# sokszor vannak ilyen formban az adataink, pl SPSS is gy trol
wide_df <- data.frame(subject = c(1, 2, 3, 4), sex = c("M", "F", "F", "M"),
                      control = c(7.9, 6.3, 9.5, 11.5),
                      cond1 = c(12.3, 10.6, 13.1, 13.4),
                      cond2 = c(10.7, 11.1, 13.8, 12.9))
wide_df
##   subject sex control cond1 cond2
## 1       1   M     7.9  12.3  10.7
## 2       2   F     6.3  10.6  11.1
## 3       3   F     9.5  13.1  13.8
## 4       4   M    11.5  13.4  12.9
# talakts long formatra a melt fggvnnyel
# id.vars: kategrit tartalmaz oszlop(ok), amit meg akarunk tartani
melt(wide_df, id.vars=c("subject", "sex"))
##    subject sex variable value
## 1        1   M  control   7.9
## 2        2   F  control   6.3
## 3        3   F  control   9.5
## 4        4   M  control  11.5
## 5        1   M    cond1  12.3
## 6        2   F    cond1  10.6
## 7        3   F    cond1  13.1
## 8        4   M    cond1  13.4
## 9        1   M    cond2  10.7
## 10       2   F    cond2  11.1
## 11       3   F    cond2  13.8
## 12       4   M    cond2  12.9
# talakts long formatra tovbbi opcikkal
# measure.vars: rtket, gyakorisgokat tartalmaz forrs oszlopok
# variable.name: j oszlop neve, hogy az rtk, gyakorisg honnan jn
# value.name: rtket, gyakorisgot tartalmaz j oszlop neve
long_df <- melt(wide_df, id.vars=c("subject", "sex"),
                measure.vars=c("control", "cond1", "cond2" ), 
                variable.name="condition",
                value.name="measurement")
long_df
##    subject sex condition measurement

## 3        3   F   control         9.5

## 8        4   M     cond1        13.4

Oszlopdiagramok (Bar Graphs)

  • az x tengelyen az brzoland kategria jelenik meg
  • az y tengelyen a kategrik gyakorisga vagy rtke, az oszlopok magassga jelli a kategria gyakorisgt vagy a kategrihoz tartoz rtket
  • x s y lehet folytonos s diszkrt vltoz is, ha mindkett folytonos, akkor hisztogramot hasznlunk
  • ha az adatok ordinlisak, akkor az oszlopok sorbarendezettek, ha nominlisak, akkor tetszleges sorrendek
  • a hisztogrammal ellenttben az oszlopok nem rnek egymshoz

Egyszer oszlopdiagramok - rtk brzolsa

#---Oszlopdiagramok (Bar Graphs)------------------------------------------------
### Egyszer oszlopdiagram - rtk brzolsa
# R Graphics Cookbook knyv adatait tartalmaz package s ggplot2 installlsa
# install.packages("gcookbook", dependencies = TRUE)
# install.packages("ggplot2", dependencies = TRUE)

# package-ek behvsa
library(gcookbook)
library(ggplot2)

# pg_mean dataset: Means of results from an experiment on plant growth
pg_mean
##   group weight
## 1  ctrl  5.032
## 2  trt1  4.661
## 3  trt2  5.526
## oszlopdiagram ggplot2-vel
# bar graph-ot ksztnk: geom_bar
# rtket brzolunk: stat = "identity"
ggplot(data = pg_mean, aes(x = group, y = weight)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill="#AFC0CB") +
  ggtitle("Means of results from an experiment on plant growth") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

## base oszlopdiagram
# bar graph-ot ksztnk: barplot fggvny
barplot(pg_mean$weight, names.arg = pg_mean$group,
        col = "#AFC0CB", border = FALSE,
        main = "Means of results from an experiment on plant growth")

Csoportostott oszlopdiagramok (Stacked bar graphs)

### Csoportostott oszlopdiagram
# cabbage_exp dataset
cabbage_exp
##   Cultivar Date Weight        sd  n         se
## 1      c39  d16   3.18 0.9566144 10 0.30250803
## 2      c39  d20   2.80 0.2788867 10 0.08819171
## 3      c39  d21   2.74 0.9834181 10 0.31098410
## 4      c52  d16   2.26 0.4452215 10 0.14079141
## 5      c52  d20   3.11 0.7908505 10 0.25008887
## 6      c52  d21   1.47 0.2110819 10 0.06674995
## ggplot2
# csoportosts egyms melletti oszlopokba
ggplot(cabbage_exp, aes(x = Date, y = Weight, fill = Cultivar)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge())

# csoportosts egy oszlop tbb fel osztsval
ggplot(cabbage_exp, aes(x = Date, y = Weight, fill = Cultivar)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_stack())

## base
# adatok talaktsa
cabbage_mat <- matrix(cabbage_exp$Weight, nrow = 2, byrow=TRUE,
                      dimnames = list(c("c39", "c52"), c("d16", "d20", "d21")))
cabbage_mat
##      d16  d20  d21
## c39 3.18 2.80 2.74
## c52 2.26 3.11 1.47
# oszlopsznek
mf_col <- c("#FD8210", "#3CC3BD")
# csoportosts egyms melletti oszlopokba
barplot(cabbage_mat, beside = TRUE, border = NA, col = mf_col)
# legend hozzadsa
legend("topright", row.names(cabbage_mat), pch = 15, col = mf_col)

# csoportosts egy oszlop tbb fel osztsval
barplot(cabbage_mat, border = NA, col = mf_col)
legend("topright", row.names(cabbage_mat), pch = 15, col = mf_col)

Vonaldiagramok (Line Graphs)

  • ha azt szeretnnk brzolni, hogy egy folytonos vltozt (y-tengely), hogy hogyan alakul egy msik folytonos vltoz fggvnyben (x-tengely)
  • az x-tengelyen gyakran az id van, teht az idsorok brzolsa is ebbe a kategriba tartozik, de lehet ms folytonos vltoz is, pl. egy ksrlet sorn adagolt gygyszer mennyisge
  • adott esetben ordinlis mrsi szint vltozkat is brzolhatunk ilyen mdon, de nominlisakat nem

Egyszer vonaldiagramok

#---Vonaldiagramok (Line Graphs)------------------------------------------------
### Egyszer vonaldiagramok

# BOD dataset: Biochemical Oxygen Demand
BOD
##   Time demand
## 1    1    8.3
## 2    2   10.3
## 3    3   19.0
## 4    4   16.0
## 5    5   15.6
## 6    7   19.8
## ggplot2
# line graph-ot csinlunk: geom_line
# time numerikus adat
ggplot(BOD, aes(x = Time, y = demand)) + geom_line()

# ha a time faktor
BOD1 <- BOD
BOD1$Time <- factor(BOD1$Time)
# group = 1 hasznlata, hogy tudja, hogy sszetartoznka a pontok
ggplot(BOD1, aes(x = Time, y = demand, group = 1)) + geom_line()

## base
# line graph-ot csinlunk: plot fggvny type = "l" argumentummal 
plot(BOD$Time, BOD$demand, type = "l", xlab = "time", ylab = "total bill")

# y-tengely most nem idt jell, hanem ms folytonos vltoz
# data frame definilsa
dat1 <- data.frame(
  time = factor(c("Lunch","Dinner"), levels=c("Lunch","Dinner")),
  total_bill = c(14.89, 17.23)
)
dat1
##     time total_bill
## 1  Lunch      14.89
## 2 Dinner      17.23
## ggplot2
# rak brzolsa az tkezsek fggvnyben
ggplot(data = dat1, aes(x = time, y = total_bill, group = 1)) + geom_line() 

# vonal egyb opcikkal (szn, tpus, mret)
# pontok hozzadsa a geom_point-tal
ggplot(data = dat1, aes(x = time, y = total_bill, group = 1)) + 
    geom_line(colour = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1.5) + 
    geom_point(colour = "red", size = 4, shape = 21, fill = "white")

## base
plot(c(1, 2), dat1$total_bill, type = "l", xlab = "time", ylab = "", lty = 2,
     lwd = 3, col = "red")
points(c(1, 2), dat1$total_bill, pch = 21, col = "red", cex = 2, bg = "white",
       lwd = 3)

Tbbszrs vonaldiagramok

### Tbbszrs vonaldiagramok

# data frame definilsa
dat2 <- data.frame(
  sex = factor(c("Female", "Female", "Male", "Male")),
  time = factor(c("Lunch", "Dinner", "Lunch", "Dinner"),
  levels = c("Lunch", "Dinner")),
  total_bill = c(13.53, 16.81, 16.24, 17.42))
dat2
##      sex   time total_bill
## 1 Female  Lunch      13.53
## 2 Female Dinner      16.81
## 3   Male  Lunch      16.24
## 4   Male Dinner      17.42
## ggplot2
# a nem szerint szeretnnk tbb vonalat: group = sex
# a sznezst is a nem szerint szeretnnk: colour = sex
ggplot(data = dat2, aes(x = time, y = total_bill, group = sex, colour = sex)) +
  geom_line() + geom_point() + ggtitle("Average Bill for Two People") + 
  xlab("Time of day") + ylab("Total bill") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

## base
# adat talaktsa
dat2_mat <- matrix(dat2$total_bill, nrow = 2, byrow=TRUE, 
                   dimnames = list(c("Female", "Male"), c("Lunch", "Dinner")))
dat2_mat
##        Lunch Dinner
## Female 13.53  16.81
## Male   16.24  17.42
par(cex = 1.2, cex.axis = 1.1)
matplot(dat2_mat, type = "b", lty = 1, pch = 19, col = mf_col, cex = 1.5, 
        lwd = 3, las = 1, bty = "n", xaxt = "n", xlim = c(0.7, 2.2), 
        ylim = c(12,18), xlab = "Time of day", ylab = "Total bill",
        main = "Average Bill for Two People")
mtext("Lunch", side = 1, at = 1)
mtext("Dinner", side = 1, at = 2)
legend("topleft", c("Lunch", "Dinner"), pch = 15, col = mf_col)

Pontfelhdiagramok/szrsdiagramok (Scatter plots)

  • kt folytonos vltoz kapcsolatt brzoljuk vele
  • minden megfigyels egy kln pont a ploton
  • gyakran illesztenek a pontfelhre vonalakat, grbket is vmilyen statisztikai modell szerint

Egyszer szrsdiagramok

#---Pontfelhdiagramok/szrsdiagramok (Scatter plots)--------------------------
### Egyszer szrsdiagramok

set.seed(955)
# data frame definilsa
dat3 <- data.frame(cond = rep(c("A", "B"), each = 10),
                   xvar = 1:20 + rnorm(20, sd = 3),
                   yvar = 1:20 + rnorm(20, sd = 3))
head(dat3)
##   cond      xvar         yvar
## 1    A -4.252354  3.473157275
## 2    A  1.702318  0.005939612
## 3    A  4.323054 -0.094252427
## 4    A  1.780628  2.072808278
## 5    A 11.537348  1.215440358
## 6    A  6.672130  3.608111411
## ggplot2
# scatter plot: geom_point
# shape = 1 res karika
ggplot(dat3, aes(x = xvar, y = yvar)) + geom_point(shape = 1)

## base
# scatter plotot csinlunk: plot fggvny defaultja
plot(dat3$xvar, dat3$yvar)

## ggplot2
# lineris regresszi illesztse 95%-os konfidencia intervallummal
ggplot(dat3, aes(x = xvar, y = yvar)) + geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm)

# konfidencia intervallum nlkl
ggplot(dat3, aes(x = xvar, y = yvar)) + geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = FALSE)

# loess grbe
ggplot(dat3, aes(x = xvar, y = yvar)) + geom_point(shape = 1) +
  geom_smooth(method = loess)

## base
# ugyanaz, mint elbb, csak formulval
plot(yvar ~ xvar, dat3)
fitline <- lm(dat3$yvar ~ dat3$xvar)
abline(fitline)

Csoportra bontott szrsdiagramok

  • amikor egy kategria szerint el szeretnk klnteni a pontfelht
### Csoportra bontott szrsdiagramok

## ggplot2
# kondci szerint sznekre sztbontva
# lineris regresszis vonallal
ggplot(dat3, aes(x = xvar, y = yvar, color = cond)) + 
  geom_point(shape = 1) + 
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = FALSE, fullrange = TRUE)

# kondci szerint formkra sztbontva
ggplot(dat3, aes(x = xvar, y = yvar, shape = cond)) + 
  geom_point()

## base
plot(dat3$xvar, dat3$yvar, col = dat3$cond)

plot(dat3$xvar, dat3$yvar, pch = unclass(dat3$cond))
legend("bottomright", legend = levels(dat3$cond), pch = c(1:3))

Eloszlsok brzolsa

Hisztogramok s srsgfggvnyek

  • az elfordulsi gyakorisgokat hisztogram segtsgvel brzolhatjuk
  • ezek az elmleti srsgfggvnyek kzeltsei
  • mindkt vltoz folytonos, y tengelyen az x tengelyen lv vltoz gyakorisgai
#---Eloszlsok brzolsa-------------------------------------------------------
### Hisztogramok s srsgfggvnyek
# faithful dataset: Old Faithful Geyser Data
head(faithful)
##   eruptions waiting
## 1     3.600      79
## 2     1.800      54
## 3     3.333      74
## 4     2.283      62
## 5     4.533      85
## 6     2.883      55
## ggplot2
# hisztogram: geom_histogram
ggplot(faithful, aes(x = waiting)) + geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

# alapbl tl sok bin-re van osztva az adat, tl finom feloszts
# a binek nagysgt a binwidth argumentummal tudjuk vltoztatni
ggplot(faithful, aes(x = waiting)) +
 geom_histogram(binwidth = 5, fill = "white", colour = "black")

### hisztogram
## base
# hist fggvny
hist(faithful$waiting)

# breaks argumnetummal tudunk lltani
hist(faithful$waiting, breaks = 6)

### srsgfggvny grbje
## ggplot2
# srsgfggvny grbje: geom_density
ggplot(faithful, aes(x = waiting)) + geom_density()

# hisztogram s srsgfggvny grbje egytt
## ggplot2
ggplot(faithful, aes(x = waiting)) + 
    geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), binwidth = 5, 
                   colour = "black", fill = "white") +
    geom_density(alpha = .2, fill = "#FF6666")

## base
hist(faithful$waiting, prob = TRUE,
     main = "Histogram and density plot of life expentancy",
     xlab = "Life expentancy",
     ylab = "Density")
lines(density(faithful$waiting))
polygon(density(faithful$waiting), col = alpha("#FF6666", 0.2))

### tlag berajzolsa
## ggplot2
# fggleges vonal: geom_vline (vzszintes vonal: geom_hline)
ggplot(faithful, aes(x = waiting)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = 5, colour = "black", fill = "white") +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(waiting)),
               color = "red", linetype = "dashed", size = 1)

## base
hist(faithful$waiting)
abline(v = mean(faithful$waiting), col = "red", lwd = 2, lty = 1)

### Tbb csoport hisztogramja s srsgfggvny grbje
# data frame definilsa
set.seed(1234)
dat4 <- data.frame(cond = factor(rep(c("A","B"), each = 200)), 
                   rating = c(rnorm(200), rnorm(200, mean = .8)))

## ggplot2
# hisztogram
ggplot(dat4, aes(x = rating, fill = cond)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = .5, alpha = .5, position = "identity")

# srsgfggvny
ggplot(dat4, aes(x = rating, colour = cond)) + geom_density()

## base
# hisztogram
hist(subset(dat4, cond == "A")$rating, 
     col = rgb(0, 0, 1, 1/4), xlim = c(-5, 5))
hist(subset(dat4, cond == "B")$rating, 
     col = rgb(1, 0, 0, 1/4), xlim = c(-5, 5),
     breaks = 10, add = T)

# srsgfggvny
plot(density(subset(dat4, cond == "A")$rating), 
     col = rgb(0, 0, 1, 1/4))
lines(density(subset(dat4, cond == "B")$rating), 
     col = rgb(1, 0, 0, 1/4))

Box plotok

### Box plotok
## ggplot2
# geom_boxplot
ggplot(dat4, aes(x = cond, y = rating, fill=cond)) + geom_boxplot()

## base
# boxplot fggvny
boxplot(dat4$rating ~ dat4$cond, data = dat4, col=c('mistyrose', 'powderblue'))

Plotok kimentse

#---Plotok kimentse------------------------------------------------------------
# j mappa ltrehozsa a plotoknak
dir.create("fig/part01", showWarnings = FALSE)

## ggplot2
ggplot(dat4, aes(x = cond, y = rating, fill=cond)) + geom_boxplot()

# amilyen kiterjesztst megadunk a fjlnvben, olyanba menti ki
# pdf, jpeg, svg, eps, png stb.
ggsave("fig/part01/ggplot2_boxplot.png", width = 10, height = 5, dpi = 100)

## base
# pdf, svg, png stb. fggvnyek attl fggen, hogy mibe szeretnnk menteni
png("fig/part01/base_boxplot.png", width = 960, height = 560, res = 120)
boxplot(dat4$rating ~ dat4$cond, data = dat4, col=c('mistyrose', 'powderblue'))
dev.off()
